# Condition

**Object**

The object for defining a condition that, when met, causes conditional properties to go into effect.

## Declaration

```swift
object Condition
```

## Discussion

Use the `Condition` object to define the condition under which the associated properties are applied.

You can use this object in [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalComponent], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalContainer], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalSection], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalText], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalComponentLayout], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalComponentStyle], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalComponentTextStyle], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalTextStyle], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalDocumentStyle], [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalDivider], and [doc://com.apple.applenews/documentation/AppleNewsFormat/ConditionalAutoPlacement].

### Example

```json
{
  "components": [
    {
      "role": "photo",
      "URL": "bundle://summer.jpg",
      "layout": "exampleLayout",
      "caption": "Thanks to the record drought, mountain lions have begun to descend from the peaks.",
      "hidden": false,
      "conditional": {
        "hidden": true,
        "conditions": {
          "maxViewportWidth": 320
        }
      }
    }
  ],
  "componentLayouts": {
    "exampleLayout": {
      "ignoreDocumentMargin": true,
      "conditional": [
        {
          "ignoreDocumentMargin": false,
          "conditions": [
            {
              "minViewportWidth": 768
            }
          ]
        }
      ]
    }
  }
}
```

## Conditional Design Elements

- **ConditionalComponent**: The object for defining conditional properties for a component, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalComponentLayout**: The object for defining conditional properties for a component layout, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalAutoPlacement**: The object for defining conditional properties for an automatically placed component, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalSection**: The object for defining conditional properties for a section component, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalDocumentStyle**: The object for defining conditional properties for a document style, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalText**: The object for defining conditional properties for a text component, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalTextStyle**: The object for defining conditional properties for a text style, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalComponentTextStyle**: The object for defining conditional properties for a component text style, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalComponentStyle**: The object for defining conditional properties for a component style, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalContainer**: The object for defining conditional properties for a container component, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalDivider**: The object for defining conditional properties for a divider component, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
- **ConditionalButton**: The object for defining a button component’s conditional properties, and when the conditional properties are in effect.
